  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The goal of this study was to examine the effects of self-perceived lactose intolerance
      (SPLI) as it relates to calcium intake and specific health problems that have been attributed
      to reduced intake of calcium and foods from the dairy group in a nationally representative
      multi-ethnic sample of adults.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
